%PAGE
%center

What is Chaos Theory ?

%leftfill, size 5

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia (www.wikipedia.org):

Established in the 1960s, chaos theory deals with systems that have a high sensitivity to initial conditions. Examples for such systems are the atmosphere, plate tectonics, economies, and population growth.

Sensitive dependence on initial conditions

Very small changes lead to different outcomes

