%PAGE
%center

What is Iteration ?

%leftfill, size 5

The process of plugging a value into an equation, computing the result and using that result as the new value to plug into the equation. Repeating this process over and over again is iteration.

Examples:

	A microphone too close to the speaker
	A video camera pointed at the TV monitor
	Each year's population of foxes and rabbits 

