%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%
%PAGE
%center

What are fractals ?

%leftfill, size 5

Fractal is a term Benoit Mandelbrot coined to describe a Mathematical geometric object which is:

	Self-similar
		Smaller and smaller pieces of it look remarkably like the whole
	Has detail at large and small scales
		No matter how much you zoom in or out on the object, it still looks "fractured"

